AB  - This paper analyzes the different responses of economic agents to import competition, in seeking policy intervention. Economic agents are divided into three groups, capitalists, workers and the government. The following output restoring policies are considered: protection, capital importation, labour importation and technology importation. The paper concentrates on capital- intensive, technologically progressive industries using both the Heckscher-Ohlin-Samuelson and the Jones-Neary factor specific models.
